                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d744">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">860c.4016/56a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Poland</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-05-28T18:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 28, 1919, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>17. Department’s No. 9 May 21, No. 12 May 23, and No. 14 May 24.<note n="7"
                        xml:id="d744fn7">No. 14 not printed.</note> American newspapers are
                    publishing long articles giving dates and places where Jews are reported to have
                    been massacred or otherwise mistreated. Congressman Siegel has personally
                    furnished Department with another such list. Agitation this matter continues and
                    Department must know whole truth situation at once. You are requested to give
                    investigation treatment Jews by Poles and attitude Jews towards Poles precedence
                    over other matters in order to furnish Department complete report without
                    delay.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
